{
    "id": "aiutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "AIUtil",
    "description": "Give non-player characters a brain: build a walkable map, send NPCs to a spot, and make them chase targets with smart pathfinding.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/aiutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "aiutil",
        "ai",
        "npc",
        "navigation",
        "pathfinding"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "TaskUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/taskutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "GameUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/gameutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "AIUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`AIUtil` gives **non-player characters** (NPCs) — enemies, allies, wandering villagers — the ability to move around your world intelligently. Instead of you steering them, they use **pathfinding** to figure out how to walk to a spot, going around walls and obstacles on their own."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "important",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Every method takes the `uniscript` of the NPC you're controlling — usually `this` on the NPC's own script."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Step 1 — Set up the NPC and the map"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Two things are needed before an NPC can navigate: the object must become an NPC, and the level needs a **navigation map** that marks where it's possible to walk."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`AddNpcController(this)`", "Turns the object into a pathfinding NPC."],
                ["`GenerateNavigation(this)`", "Builds the walkable map of the level so NPCs know where they can go."],
                ["`UpdateAgentDimensions(this)`", "Refreshes the NPC's size (radius/height) used for navigation."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "class Enemy",
                "{",
                "    void OnInit()",
                "    {",
                "        AIUtil.AddNpcController(this);",
                "        AIUtil.GenerateNavigation(this);   // build the walkable map once",
                "    }",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Step 2 — Send the NPC somewhere"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`SetNavigationTarget` tells the NPC where to go; it returns `true` if a path was found. Use `StartNavigation` and `StopNavigation` to control whether it's actually moving."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetNavigationTarget(this, position)`", "Sets a destination; returns `true` if the NPC can reach it."],
                ["`StartNavigation(this)`", "Starts the NPC moving along its path."],
                ["`StopNavigation(this)`", "Stops the NPC where it is."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Walk the enemy to where the player is standing.",
                "vector3 target = UniObjectUtil.GetWorldPosition(player);",
                "if (AIUtil.SetNavigationTarget(this, target))",
                "{",
                "    AIUtil.StartNavigation(this);",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Chasing targets"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Instead of setting a position by hand, you can give the NPC **targets** to react to — for example, chase the nearest player."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`AddTargetObject(this, target)`", "Adds an object the NPC should pay attention to."],
                ["`RemoveTargetObject(this, target)`", "Removes a target."],
                ["`AssignTargetsAutomatically(this, targetTag)`", "Automatically uses every object with the given tag as a target."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Treat everything tagged \"player\" as something to chase.",
                "AIUtil.AssignTargetsAutomatically(this, \"player\");"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Advanced controls"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`ResetSettings(this)`", "Resets the NPC's navigation settings to their defaults."],
                ["`ExternalEvent(this, eventCode, value)`", "Sends a custom signal to the NPC's behavior (e.g. \"alert\" or \"flee\")."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-019",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`GenerateNavigation`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddNpcController`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`UpdateAgentDimensions`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`bool`", "`SetNavigationTarget`", "`uniscript, vector3 position`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddTargetObject`", "`uniscript, uniscript target`"],
                ["`void`", "`RemoveTargetObject`", "`uniscript, uniscript target`"],
                ["`void`", "`StartNavigation`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`StopNavigation`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AssignTargetsAutomatically`", "`uniscript, string targetTag`"],
                ["`void`", "`ResetSettings`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`ExternalEvent`", "`uniscript, int eventCode, object value`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-020",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Build the navigation map with `GenerateNavigation` once after the level is set up — not every frame. Tagging your targets (see [UniObjectUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil#block-030)) makes `AssignTargetsAutomatically` the easiest way to wire up chasing."
        }
    ]
}
